# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->
We have to create a 2-dimensional matrix of size n x n such that the elements are filled in spiral form.

# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
**Follow the code below to understand the solution.**

      **If this solution helped you, give it an up-vote to help others** 


# Complexity
- Time complexity: O(N^2)
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

- Space complexity: O(N^2)
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

# Code
```
class Solution {
    public int[][] generateMatrix(int n) {


        int [][] arr = new int[n][n];

        int i = 0;      //starting row index
        int j = 0;      //starting col index

        int k = n;    //ending row index
        int l = n;    //ending col index

        int count = 0;

        boolean flag = true;

        while(flag) {

            flag = false;


            //--------------LEFT --->> RIGHT------------//
            while(j < l)
            {
              arr[i][j] = ++count;
              j++;
                flag = true;
            }
            j--;
            i++;


            //-------------TOP --->> BOTTOM-------------//

            while (i < k) {
                arr[i][j] = ++count;
                i++;
                flag = true;
            }
            j--;
            i--;
            k--;

            //-----------RIGHT --->> LEFT---------//
            while (j >= n - l) {
                arr[i][j] = ++count;
                j--;
                flag = true;
            }
            j++;
            l--;
            i--;

            //----------BOTTOM --->> TOP-------------//
            while (i >= n - k) {
                arr[i][j] = ++count;
                i--;
                flag = true;
            }
            i++;
            j++;
        }


        return arr;
    }
}
```

