# Logic :
If the given string is made up of repeated substrings, then the lengths of those repeated substrings will be a factor of the length of the given string.

#### Example :

String of length 10.
xxxxxxxxxx

The factors of 10 = 5, 2, 1.

So, the repeated string can be of length 5, 2, 1.
xxxxx xxxxx
xx xx xx xx xx
x x x x x x x x x x.

abcdeabcde, "abcde" is repeated.
ababababab, "ab" is repeated.
aaaaaaaaaaa, "a" is repeated.

# Solution :
* Loop through the factors of the length of the given string.
* Using Sliding Window Approach, find out all the substrings taking the factors as the lengths of substrings. These substrings start after the previous substring has ended.
* Find out if all the substrings are equal, return true if such repetition is found.
* Return false, if no such repetition is found.

The solution is more efficient if we take the factors in descending order.

#### Implementation :
```
class Solution {
    public boolean repeatedSubstringPattern(String s) 
    {
        int len = s.length();
        int div=2;
        while(div<=len)
        {
            if(len%div==0)
            {
                int windowSize = len/div;
                // window size is equal to the factor
                String firstSubString = s.substring(0,windowSize);
                int start = windowSize;
                boolean substringRepeated = false;
                // Loop through all the remaining substrings
                while(start<len)
                {
                    String nextSubString = s.substring(start,start+windowSize);
                    start += windowSize;
                    if(firstSubString.equals(nextSubString)==false)
                    {
                        substringRepeated = false;
                        break;
                    }
                    substringRepeated = true;
                }
                if(substringRepeated)
                {
                    return true;
                }
            }
            div++;
        }
        return false;
    }
}
```

